race.comment: Open race but giving SHOCKLETZ (1) one more chance at much better odds than she's been her past couple. Te fresh win was good although she did have cover from a strong wind. She didn't have much room at Flemington and then got back in a strange race at Cranbourne on a tricky track. Now gets to 2500m on the big deck here, that's her ideal scenario and she can bounce back. TEXAS TEA (12) finished ahead of SHOCKLETZ at Cranbourne with a better run in transit, sticking on well for a narrow fourth. Gets the senior jockey aboard and rolls forward which sees him hard to catch. TIKEMYSON (3) is racing consistently and can give a sight. Chances don't end there. BLACK PEPPERMINT (4) closed strongly to score at Cranbourne last start over 2540m and this looks within his grasp on the back of that effort.
